\f3\fs16 NAME\par
    C:\\XS_Inventory.ps1\par
\par
SYNOPSIS\par
    Creates an inventory of a XenServer 8.2 CU1 Pool.\par
\par
\par
SYNTAX\par
    C:\\XS_Inventory.ps1 -ServerName <String> [-User <String>] [-HTML] [-Text] [-Folder <String>] [-Section\par
    <String[]>] [-NoPoolMemory] [-NoPoolStorage] [-NoPoolNetworking] [-AddDateTime] [-Dev] [-Log] [-ScriptInfo]\par
    [-ReportFooter] [-SmtpPort <Int32>] [-SmtpServer <String>] [-From <String>] [-To <String>] [-UseSSL]\par
    [<CommonParameters>]\par
\par
    C:\\XS_Inventory.ps1 -ServerName <String> [-User <String>] [-HTML] [-Text] [-Folder <String>] [-Section\par
    <String[]>] [-NoPoolMemory] [-NoPoolStorage] [-NoPoolNetworking] [-AddDateTime] [-Dev] [-Log] [-ScriptInfo]\par
    [-ReportFooter] [-MSWord] [-PDF] [-CompanyAddress <String>] [-CompanyEmail <String>] [-CompanyFax <String>]\par
    [-CompanyName <String>] [-CompanyPhone <String>] [-CoverPage <String>] [-UserName <String>] [-SmtpPort <Int32>]\par
    [-SmtpServer <String>] [-From <String>] [-To <String>] [-UseSSL] [<CommonParameters>]\par
\par
\par
DESCRIPTION\par
    Creates a complete inventory of a XenServer 8.2 CU1 Pool using Microsoft Word, PDF, formatted\par
    text, HTML, and PowerShell.\par
\par
    The script requires at least PowerShell version 4 but runs best in version 5.\par
\par
    Word is NOT needed to run the script. This script outputs in Text and HTML.\par
    The default output format is HTML.\par
\par
    Creates an output file named Poolname.<fileextension>.\par
\par
    Word and PDF documents include a Cover Page, Table of Contents, and Footer.\par
    Includes support for the following language versions of Microsoft Word:\par
        Catalan\par
        Danish\par
        Dutch\par
        English\par
        Finnish\par
        French\par
        German\par
        Norwegian\par
        Portuguese\par
        Spanish\par
        Swedish\par
\par
\par
PARAMETERS\par
    -ServerName <String>\par
        Specifies which XenServer Pool to use to run the script against.\par
\par
        You can enter the ServerName as the NetBIOS name, FQDN, or IP Address.\par
\par
        If entered as an IP address, the script attempts o determine and use the actual\par
        pool or Pool Master name.\par
\par
        ServerName should be the Pool Master. If you use a Slave host, the script attempts\par
        to determine the Pool Master and then makes a connection attempt to the Pool Master.\par
        If successful, the script continues. If not successful, the script ends.\par
\par
        Required?                    true\par
        Position?                    named\par
        Default value\par
        Accept pipeline input?       false\par
        Accept wildcard characters?  false\par
\par
    -User <String>\par
        Username to use for the connection to the XenServer Pool.\par
\par
        Required?                    false\par
        Position?                    named\par
        Default value\par
        Accept pipeline input?       false\par
        Accept wildcard characters?  false\par
\par
    -HTML [<SwitchParameter>]\par
        Creates an HTML file with an .html extension.\par
\par
        HTML is the default report format.\par
\par
        This parameter is set to True   If no other output format is selected.\par
\par
        Required?                    false\par
        Position?                    named\par
        Default value                False\par
        Accept pipeline input?       false\par
        Accept wildcard characters?  false\par
\par
    -Text [<SwitchParameter>]\par
        Creates a formatted text file with a .txt extension.\par
        Text formatting is based on the default tab spacing of 8 by Microsoft Notepad.\par
\par
        This parameter is disabled by default.\par
\par
        Required?                    false\par
        Position?                    named\par
        Default value                False\par
        Accept pipeline input?       false\par
        Accept wildcard characters?  false\par
\par
    -Folder <String>\par
        Specifies the optional output folder to save the output report.\par
\par
        Required?                    false\par
        Position?                    named\par
        Default value\par
        Accept pipeline input?       false\par
        Accept wildcard characters?  false\par
\par
    -Section <String[]>\par
        Processes one or more sections of the report.\par
        Valid options are:\par
                Pool\par
                Host\par
                SharedStorage\par
                VM (Virtual Machines)\par
                All\par
\par
        This parameter defaults to All sections.\par
\par
        A comma separates multiple sections. -Section host, pool\par
\par
        Required?                    false\par
        Position?                    named\par
        Default value                All\par
        Accept pipeline input?       false\par
        Accept wildcard characters?  false\par
\par
    -NoPoolMemory [<SwitchParameter>]\par
        Excludes Pool Memory information from the output document.\par
\par
        This Switch is helpful in large XenServer pools, where there may be many hosts.\par
\par
        This parameter is disabled by default.\par
        This parameter has an alias of NPM.\par
\par
        Required?                    false\par
        Position?                    named\par
        Default value                False\par
        Accept pipeline input?       false\par
        Accept wildcard characters?  false\par
\par
    -NoPoolStorage [<SwitchParameter>]\par
        Excludes Pool Storage information from the output document.\par
\par
        This Switch is helpful in large XenServer pools, where there may be many storage\par
        repositories and hosts.\par
\par
        This parameter is disabled by default.\par
        This parameter has an alias of NPS.\par
\par
        Required?                    false\par
        Position?                    named\par
        Default value                False\par
        Accept pipeline input?       false\par
        Accept wildcard characters?  false\par
\par
    -NoPoolNetworking [<SwitchParameter>]\par
        Excludes Pool Networking information from the output document.\par
\par
        This Switch is helpful in large XenServer pools, where there may be many hosts.\par
\par
        This parameter is disabled by default.\par
        This parameter has an alias of NPN.\par
\par
        Required?                    false\par
        Position?                    named\par
        Default value                False\par
        Accept pipeline input?       false\par
        Accept wildcard characters?  false\par
\par
    -AddDateTime [<SwitchParameter>]\par
        Adds a date timestamp to the end of the file name.\par
\par
        The timestamp is in the format of yyyy-MM-dd_HHmm.\par
        June 1, 2024, at 6 PM is 2024-06-01_1800.\par
\par
        The output filename will be ReportName_2024-06-01_1800.<ext>.\par
\par
        This parameter is disabled by default.\par
        This parameter has an alias of ADT.\par
\par
        Required?                    false\par
        Position?                    named\par
        Default value                False\par
        Accept pipeline input?       false\par
        Accept wildcard characters?  false\par
\par
    -Dev [<SwitchParameter>]\par
        Clears errors at the beginning of the script.\par
        Outputs all errors to a text file at the end of the script.\par
\par
        This is used when the script developer requests more troubleshooting data.\par
        The text file is placed in the same folder from where the script is run.\par
\par
        This parameter is disabled by default.\par
\par
        Required?                    false\par
        Position?                    named\par
        Default value                False\par
        Accept pipeline input?       false\par
        Accept wildcard characters?  false\par
\par
    -Log [<SwitchParameter>]\par
        Generates a log file for troubleshooting.\par
\par
        Required?                    false\par
        Position?                    named\par
        Default value                False\par
        Accept pipeline input?       false\par
        Accept wildcard characters?  false\par
\par
    -ScriptInfo [<SwitchParameter>]\par
        Outputs information about the script to a text file.\par
        The text file is placed in the same folder from where the script is run.\par
\par
        This parameter is disabled by default.\par
        This parameter has an alias of SI.\par
\par
        Required?                    false\par
        Position?                    named\par
        Default value                False\par
        Accept pipeline input?       false\par
        Accept wildcard characters?  false\par
\par
    -ReportFooter [<SwitchParameter>]\par
        Outputs a footer section at the end of the report.\par
\par
        This parameter has an alias of RF.\par
\par
        Report Footer\par
                Report information:\par
                        Created with: <Script Name> - Release Date: <Script Release Date>\par
                        Script version: <Script Version>\par
                        Started on <Date Time in Local Format>\par
                        Elapsed time: nn days, nn hours, nn minutes, nn.nn seconds\par
                        Ran from domain <Domain Name> by user <Username>\par
                        Ran from the folder <Folder Name>\par
\par
        Script Name and Script Release date are script-specific variables.\par
        Start Date Time in Local Format is a script variable.\par
        Elapsed time is a calculated value.\par
        Domain Name is $env:USERDNSDOMAIN.\par
        Username is $env:USERNAME.\par
        Folder Name is a script variable.\par
\par
        Required?                    false\par
        Position?                    named\par
        Default value                False\par
        Accept pipeline input?       false\par
        Accept wildcard characters?  false\par
\par
    -MSWord [<SwitchParameter>]\par
        SaveAs DOCX file\par
\par
        Microsoft Word is no longer the default report format.\par
        This parameter is disabled by default.\par
\par
        Required?                    false\par
        Position?                    named\par
        Default value                False\par
        Accept pipeline input?       false\par
        Accept wildcard characters?  false\par
\par
    -PDF [<SwitchParameter>]\par
        SaveAs PDF file instead of DOCX file.\par
\par
        The PDF file is roughly 5X to 10X larger than the DOCX file.\par
\par
        This parameter requires Microsoft Word to be installed.\par
        This parameter uses Word's SaveAs PDF capability.\par
\par
        This parameter is disabled by default.\par
\par
        Required?                    false\par
        Position?                    named\par
        Default value                False\par
        Accept pipeline input?       false\par
        Accept wildcard characters?  false\par
\par
    -CompanyAddress <String>\par
        Company Address to use for the Cover Page   If the Cover Page has the Address field.\par
\par
        The following Cover Pages have an Address field:\par
                Banded (Word 2013/2016)\par
                Contrast (Word 2010)\par
                Exposure (Word 2010)\par
                Filigree (Word 2013/2016)\par
                Ion (Dark) (Word 2013/2016)\par
                Retrospect (Word 2013/2016)\par
                Semaphore (Word 2013/2016)\par
                Tiles (Word 2010)\par
                ViewMaster (Word 2013/2016)\par
\par
        This parameter is only valid with the MSWORD and PDF output parameters.\par
        This parameter has an alias of CA.\par
\par
        Required?                    false\par
        Position?                    named\par
        Default value\par
        Accept pipeline input?       false\par
        Accept wildcard characters?  false\par
\par
    -CompanyEmail <String>\par
        Company Email to use for the Cover Page   If the Cover Page has the Email field.\par
\par
        The following Cover Pages have an Email field:\par
                Facet (Word 2013/2016)\par
\par
        This parameter is only valid with the MSWORD and PDF output parameters.\par
        This parameter has an alias of CE.\par
\par
        Required?                    false\par
